content: This app is really good and values are within ranges! I gave a 4 because the other features within the app (links, etc) do not work, so that is disappointing.
Amazing.
Great app
I used this app over the years. Its very handy, especially the lab values.
I like it. I use it quite frequently! I recommend it to all my new orientees.   Nuff said?
Yup it's good. Now I know definitively what's wrong with me.
I like this App but free Quick Lab Values App still better.
Nice
Thx for the update, apps is up an running great on my p780 lenovo kitkat 4.4.2
it crashes all the time. it won't even start :-/
Definitely a very helpful app. Would buy again in a heartbeat!
Excellent

I am a medical student and I used this app very frequently during my third year! It helped out numerous times and is well worth the $3.  I agree with the other reviewer saying that it is annoying to have to agree to the terms every time the app is opened, but I don't think that drops the quality of the app at all. A check box saying never to show it again would be nice though!  But all in all I really like this app and it helped me out a ton!
Very useful app
Quite a helpful program when you need to remember many lab values! Would be better if app was developed for tablets.
Nice
Useful rapid lab. reference
It would be a nice thing to have lab tests arranged in hepatic functional,  kidney functional a so.
Really nice and complete !!! A dream app for student nurses and great reference for experienced nurses !!!

Great app, very useful. Would like to see not only a description, but the purpose of the overall panel tests. Also would like to see obstetric labs and panels as well, as they are just as impoetant!! Please and thanks
I love tis app.

Hoped for a bit more. Would like a 'specialty' sorting(I.e. urology,gyno) Missing some labs like urine culture, urine cytology I needed so I had to look values up individually which prevents a quick reference
this app is very useful.  best medical app id ever seen. best for nurses!
Descriptions arn't great -> There's better (more comprehensive) medical reference applications in the Play store.
I am a nursing student and this app is beautiful and I will use this constantly, especially in med-surge!
Nice app..easy for student like me..if u can include more standard values that would be great!!!
I wish I had this back in nursing school. It is also a great refresher.
great app.
Sangat bermanfaat infonya.. Nice work in my Galaxy Note
The most informative app I've seen.
Fantastic
Great app for school
just what you need to know at your fingertips. I have been looking for this type of info for a long time. Yippee !
Perfekt til medicinstuderende.
Awesome app! I'm in Medical  school, works great for me.  :)
Would like to see titers for hepatitis, varicalla, mmr, etc. Then it would be 10 stars!
I love this app, and the ability to add, and edit labs is a major plus. The hit a home run with this one.

I am an MT and I use this app, mainly for the reference ranges. This app is very well done and I recommend it highly. It is easy to read, scroll and navigate through the various sections. There is a lot of data packed in this app, and it is well organized. The developer did a good job.  StraightTalk Android Optimus Q 2.3.4
I'm a nurse & this is an awesome app!!! Would like 2 see labs for STDs added.
Great apps and great online help....worth every penny.
Perfect lab and medical app i have come across..
I love having all this medical knowledge in the palm of my hands. It is great for studying and quick reference. I highly recommend it!

I'm a 4th year medical student and I this is the best lab values app I've used so far. It's frustrating sometimes because Android doesn't have the best medical apps but finally here's one that is fantastic.  Lab descriptions are spot on.  High/low differentials has been really helpful when working up my patients.  Really nice that you can edit labs and add comments if you need. I have an old Droid that is pretty slow and it runs great on it.  If you need a lab values app, go for this one.
